gomodel:SYNGO_1968  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Representative electron microscopic images showing Reticulon-4 receptor immunoreactive gold particles in the presynaptic compartment in the motor cortex.\n\n24/11/2017 Pim\n- Most immunoparticles seem to be present on SVs. This annotation is not made because the presumed function is on the plasma membrane, but this is not shown in the paper.. Experimental description: \"Adult male Sprague Dawley rats (5- 6 weeks, 190-220 g; Janvier)\nwere used for LTP, LTD, in vivo motor learning, and electron microscopy experiments.\". p. 8686" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
